1) Open up a terminal and have mongod running (sudo mongod)
2) Open up a terminal, go to the project root folder, and run nodemon (nodemon server.js)
3) Open up a terminal, go to the project root folder, go to angular folder (probably named Public), run (ng build --watch)
4) Go to localhost:8000

to tweak DB:
1) type "mongo" in terminal
2) open up db you want to use (eg "use beeriokart")
3) delete stuff (eg db.races.drop())